
Task: Automate search and simulate native mouse/keyboard actions with Robot Class

Steps:
1. Navigate to: https://duckduckgo.com/
2. Focus on the search input field.
3. Copy the string "Selenium Robot Class" to clipboard using Robot and paste it with Ctrl + V.
4. Press Enter using Robot to start the search.
5. Wait until the first search result title becomes visible.
6. Move mouse to top-right corner of the screen and left-click.
   Note: Mouse coordinates should be dynamically calculated using screen resolution.
7. Move mouse to bottom-left corner and right-click.
   Again, coordinates must be resolution-aware.
8. Close the browser.

